## Quick Reference: Common Refactoring Patterns

### Pattern 1: Replace Loading State Boilerplate

**Before (30 lines):**
```typescript
const [data, setData] = useState(null);
const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
const [error, setError] = useState(null);

useEffect(() => {
  const load = async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    try {
      const res = await Bridge.getData();
      if (res.success) setData(res.data);
      else setError(res.error);
    } catch (e) {
      setError(e.message);
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };
  load();
}, []);
```

**After (3 lines):**
```typescript
const { data, loading, error } = useBridgeQuery({
  queryFn: () => Bridge.getData()
});
```

